Document: RootMotionView
Path: godot/classes/class_rootmotionview.rst
Summary: RootMotionView class reference with inheritance and basic description.

RootMotionView is a class used to visualize and manipulate root motion in Godot. It inherits from Node and provides tools for animators to adjust character movement through animation curves. The class is part of the animation system and is typically used in conjunction with AnimationPlayer and AnimationTree nodes. Key features include the ability to display motion paths, adjust speed multipliers, and synchronize with animation timelines. RootMotionView is particularly useful for fine-tuning character movement in complex animation setups.
